==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: put up
<hw>put up</hw> <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>to connect a
device to a telephone line surreptitiously, so as to listen to or record
the conversations of persons on the telephone without their knowledge;
-- of telephones, persons, or locations. Used as police jargon.</def>
<mark>[jargon]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> wiretap, tap, intercept, bug.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>] [<source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Put-up</ent>⟦br⟧
